name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: Silence has also taught me the art of listening. True listening. I mean maybe some of that comes from being in the army as I have some hearing loss, but really, even as a kid I always liked to listen to everything mespecially when I was outside. I love listening to nature.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: Silence was once a strange concept.  To me, silence was something to fear and something you “definitely wanted to avoid. “ Now, I cherish it almost as much as air. I feel I can truly connect with my whole self and honestly, I love hearing my own thoughts. That shit is dope.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: I feel like sometimes I will intentionally listen to music just so I can distract my thoughts but it hits different when you want to hear each and every thought- you don’t want to miss a beat. I love listening to the wind in my ears, the birds in trees, the sound of LIFE.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: Sometimes I will work in absolute silence just to listen to my thoughts. As much as I love music, I find that just like anything else, there’s a time and a place for it. The vibe has to be right and so does the song. But one of the things I cherish most is hearing my thoughts.

tweet: Also on that same note, whenever I go out to eat, my personal tipping thought process is this: I always tip 20-25% of my check regardless of the service. Why? Because I have empathy for those that may bust their ass and provide excellent service and still get no tip.
